{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VkFiF4U7DgtmCvxeEW4oTG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’---\n     2â†’name: deterministic-service-test\n     3â†’description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4â†’---\n     5â†’\n     6â†’# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7â†’\n     8â†’Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9â†’\n    10â†’## Required Variables\n    11â†’\n    12â†’- `service_symbol`\n    13â†’- `module_path`\n    14â†’- `create_method`\n    15â†’- `cancel_method`\n    16â†’\n    17â†’## Execution Checklist\n    18â†’\n    19â†’1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20â†’2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21â†’3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22â†’4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23â†’5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24â†’\n    25â†’## Guardrails\n    26â†’\n    27â†’- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28â†’- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29â†’- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30â†’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1a78742-c3de-412a-8e9c-5435c1085852","uuid":"bc7e232e-18a3-4ebf-a330-6ff4289997de"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PduCXYcGSXfi3zGijoJkGW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist, not malicious.\n\nFollowing the `deterministic-service-test` skill for `CoreService` (`services.core_service`) with methods `create_record` and `cancel_record`:\n\n**Execution Checklist:**\n\n1. **Deterministic inputs** â€” Fix time via `freezegun`/injected clock, pin IDs/UUIDs, seed randomness; never call `datetime.now()` or `uuid4()` inside assertions.\n2. **One behavior per test** â€” Separate tests: `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent`, etc.\n3. **Visible `# Act` section** â€” Each test has `# Arrange` / `# Act` / `# Assert` comments with the service call under `# Act`.\n4. **Boundary mocks with autospec** â€” Mock only repositories, clocks, external clients via `create_autospec(CoreService, ...)` or `mocker.patch(\"services.core_service.<boundary>\", autospec=True)`. Do not mock `CoreService` internals.\n5. **No shared mutable state** â€” Build fresh fixtures per test; avoid module-level lists/dicts; prefer function-scoped pytest fixtures.\n\n**Guardrails:**\n\n- Use pytest functions, not `unittest.TestCase` subclasses.\n- Inject a frozen clock and seeded RNG; no real `time`/`random` calls.\n- Assert observable behavior (return value, repository call, emitted event) â€” not internal attribute churn.\n\n**Suggested test skeleton (pseudocode, not written to disk):**\n\n```\n# tests/services/test_core_service.py\nfrom unittest.mock import create_autospec\nimport pytest\nfrom services.core_service import CoreService\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef repo(): return create_autospec(SomeRepo, instance=True)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef clock(): return lambda: FIXED_DT\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef service(repo, clock): return CoreService(repo=repo, clock=clock)\n\ndef test_create_record_persists_with_fixed_timestamp(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    payload = {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"name\": \"x\"}\n    # Act\n    result = service.create_record(payload)\n    # Assert\n    repo.save.assert_called_once()\n    assert result.created_at == FIXED_DT\n\ndef test_cancel_record_marks_entity_cancelled(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    repo.get.return_value = Record(id=\"rec-1\", status=\"active\")\n    # Act\n    service.cancel_record(\"rec-1\")\n    # Assert\n    saved = repo.save.call_args.args[0]\n    assert saved.status == \"cancelled\"\n```\n\nPer project instructions, no files were created and `jig` was not invoked."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":631,"cache_read_input_tokens":21635,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":631,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":957,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1a78742-c3de-412a-8e9c-5435c1085852","uuid":"46b5c5b0-5b38-4c16-9109-623bdc51c053"}
